WEBVTT

00:15.599 --> 00:17.143
WALKER:
Previously on Powers...

00:17.351 --> 00:19.687
So, if you're watching this,
I'm probably dead.

00:19.937 --> 00:21.480
Continue your work together.

00:21.605 --> 00:23.524
All of my assets,
including this house,

00:23.607 --> 00:26.485
and all my proprietary
technology, are yours now.

00:26.944 --> 00:28.487
Have some fucking fun.

00:29.155 --> 00:30.156
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

00:33.492 --> 00:34.827
You got to get out
of Powers Division.

00:34.952 --> 00:36.912
You think I'm gonna
leave my job here?

00:36.996 --> 00:38.414
They're coming for you!

00:38.664 --> 00:40.332
Your father
is being picked up by
the Bureau this morning,

00:40.541 --> 00:43.252
Part of an
ongoing investigation
into city corruption.

00:43.461 --> 00:46.130
If there's anything
you can do
to make this go away,

00:46.255 --> 00:47.631
I'm begging you
to do it.

00:48.299 --> 00:49.675
NICOLE: Senator Bailey Brown.

00:50.009 --> 00:51.677
He's been making
headlines recently,

00:51.802 --> 00:54.597
as he's the main player
for the anti-Powers
legislation.

00:54.889 --> 00:58.476
When the use of superpowers
becomes illegal for everyone,

00:58.559 --> 01:00.728
then and only then
can we be safe.

01:00.811 --> 01:02.813
Scandalous video
of Senator Bailey Brown

01:02.897 --> 01:04.482
emerged this morning.

01:04.565 --> 01:06.734
Now the fate of his bill
is in question,

01:06.817 --> 01:08.777
and no one can seem
to find him.

01:08.861 --> 01:10.654
I know that
you killed Janice,

01:10.738 --> 01:13.491
and I will not stop
until everybody
knows the truth.

01:13.657 --> 01:15.326
She was such a fighter.

01:15.409 --> 01:17.495
She fought right
until the end.

01:18.621 --> 01:19.622
(GRUNTS)

01:19.705 --> 01:20.748
(YELLS) Fuck! Walker!

01:20.831 --> 01:21.999
DEENA: Walker!

01:23.501 --> 01:24.752
(EXPLOSIONS)

01:24.835 --> 01:26.837
(GUNFIRE)

01:29.006 --> 01:30.508
(EXPLOSION)
(MEN YELLING)

01:35.054 --> 01:36.222
MAN: Keep your head down.

01:36.514 --> 01:38.057
Victory...

01:38.682 --> 01:39.934
is right over there.

01:42.436 --> 01:44.522
It's yours
for the taking.

01:44.980 --> 01:47.358
Take it from those

01:47.525 --> 01:51.028
murdering sons
of German bitches.

01:52.029 --> 01:55.533
That nest of vipers
is all that stands

01:55.616 --> 01:58.369
between you
and your loved ones.

01:58.452 --> 01:59.870
You're the murdering
son of a bitch.

01:59.995 --> 02:01.288
Patrick, no.

02:01.622 --> 02:03.666
(MEN SHOUTING IN BACKGROUND)

02:03.874 --> 02:05.793
(GUNFIRE CONTINUES)

02:06.919 --> 02:08.337
Did you say something?

02:10.506 --> 02:11.590
Did you?

02:11.715 --> 02:12.967
Yes, sir.

02:13.425 --> 02:14.593
Repeat it.

02:15.344 --> 02:16.595
Stop.

02:17.596 --> 02:19.098
Not these men...

02:19.640 --> 02:20.849
Not today.

02:21.100 --> 02:22.351
You coward.

02:24.853 --> 02:26.564
I'm going to have you shot.

02:29.608 --> 02:31.068
I'll save you the trouble.

02:31.151 --> 02:32.444
MAN: Suicide! No!

02:32.570 --> 02:34.238
No, Patrick, no!
(GUNFIRE)

02:36.240 --> 02:37.908
(GUNFIRE AND EXPLOSIONS)

02:43.080 --> 02:44.915
(MEN SCREAMING IN DISTANCE)

02:46.584 --> 02:48.919
(FOXHOLE CHATTER)

02:49.753 --> 02:51.922
(MEN CONTINUE
SCREAMING, YELLING)

02:55.551 --> 02:56.635
(SCREAMING STOPS)

03:36.550 --> 03:38.344
You... stop.

03:40.971 --> 03:42.598
What's your name?

03:44.391 --> 03:46.185
You can call me "death."

03:58.238 --> 03:59.490
(GUNSHOT ECHOES)

04:04.578 --> 04:06.497
(SIREN WAILING)

04:25.599 --> 04:26.934
(WHIRRING)

04:30.938 --> 04:32.690
Has he finally
showed up?

04:32.898 --> 04:33.941
No.

04:34.024 --> 04:36.068
Just dropping off
more hate mail.

04:47.788 --> 04:50.082
Oh, shit.

04:52.209 --> 04:54.002
(SIGHS)

04:54.378 --> 04:55.879
(SCREAMING)

05:03.804 --> 05:06.014
(BIRDS CHIRPING)
(WOODPECKER TAPPING)

05:10.144 --> 05:12.563
Hey, Daniel,
not too far now, okay?

05:13.897 --> 05:15.065
You ready for lunch?

05:15.315 --> 05:16.650
Not yet.

05:18.694 --> 05:20.529
Do you miss it?
What?

05:20.612 --> 05:23.031
You know,
all that crazy.

05:24.908 --> 05:27.995
No, I don't miss it
at all.

05:28.579 --> 05:29.913
Not one bit.

05:31.039 --> 05:32.583
Couldn't be happier.

05:34.042 --> 05:35.836
Make sure your brother
doesn't fall in the lake.

05:44.344 --> 05:45.763
(CELL PHONE RINGS)

05:50.809 --> 05:52.352
This is Cross.

06:15.793 --> 06:16.877
(RINGING NOISE)

06:17.127 --> 06:18.504
(SCREAMING)

06:19.463 --> 06:20.631
Fuck!

06:21.924 --> 06:23.759
(ROARING NOISE)

06:26.345 --> 06:27.638
You know, when people say
they feel like

06:27.763 --> 06:29.014
a building fell on them...

06:29.139 --> 06:31.350
That's not
what this felt like.

06:31.475 --> 06:33.060
But a building
did fall on you.

06:33.143 --> 06:35.229
And they said I was fine.

06:35.312 --> 06:36.355
Yeah.

06:37.439 --> 06:38.899
Fucking miracle.

06:42.027 --> 06:44.696
This felt like my head
was exploding,

06:44.822 --> 06:46.156
you know. three times now.

06:46.782 --> 06:48.200
I have no idea why.

06:49.159 --> 06:50.661
You should have been killed.

06:50.786 --> 06:51.829
Sure, I know that.

06:51.912 --> 06:52.955
You know, at least
broken bones

06:53.038 --> 06:54.540
or suffered a traumatic
brain injury...

06:54.665 --> 06:56.250
Something.

06:56.333 --> 06:58.001
But everything is normal.

06:58.126 --> 07:00.087
(STAMMERS) It's not normal.

07:00.295 --> 07:01.797
What? Oh, surviving that?

07:01.880 --> 07:03.674
No, it's not normal--
No, my-my head.

07:03.757 --> 07:05.133
Something's wrong.

07:05.467 --> 07:08.595
I believe you,
but I can't find anything.

07:10.097 --> 07:11.765
(SIGHS) What do you mean?

07:12.516 --> 07:15.769
I mean, I can see nothing
organic or problematic

07:15.853 --> 07:18.397
in any test that would point
to a source for your symptoms.

07:19.022 --> 07:21.024
I'm not making this up, Doc.
I...

07:21.149 --> 07:22.734
No, I didn't say that.

07:25.237 --> 07:26.989
But you have been through
a pretty serious

07:27.072 --> 07:28.657
change of circumstance,

07:29.032 --> 07:31.243
personal loss, job loss.

07:31.451 --> 07:33.036
Now, not to be glib
about this,

07:33.161 --> 07:34.705
but have you
considered PTSD?

07:36.123 --> 07:37.875
You want a second opinion?

07:37.958 --> 07:39.042
No, I want it to stop.

07:39.209 --> 07:41.003
How about you give us
a couple of days
in the hospital

07:41.086 --> 07:42.754
under observation?
No, thank you.

07:42.921 --> 07:45.090
Uh, can I just get
some painkillers?

07:45.966 --> 07:47.134
All right.

07:47.551 --> 07:49.887
Are you allergic to any
particular medication?

07:50.012 --> 07:52.556
Not that I know of, I...
(CELL PHONE RINGS)

07:53.390 --> 07:55.058
(BEEP)

07:55.392 --> 07:56.894
Walker.

07:59.187 --> 08:00.731
(SIGHS)

08:06.153 --> 08:07.779
Didn't expect
to see you here.

08:07.905 --> 08:11.116
Oh, shit.
Uh, goes both ways.

08:11.783 --> 08:13.452
Nice. (CHUCKLES)

08:14.703 --> 08:16.246
Why are you here?

08:16.747 --> 08:18.332
It's not every day
a girl gets to see

08:18.415 --> 08:19.958
her father on trial
for his life.

08:20.208 --> 08:21.752
They don't execute you
for corruption.

08:22.836 --> 08:25.213
You'd be a cop in prison.

08:25.422 --> 08:27.507
Point taken.
Yeah.

08:27.799 --> 08:29.134
What happened in there?

08:29.259 --> 08:30.761
Oh, trial's delayed.

08:30.844 --> 08:33.055
Prosecutor has some
new evidence
he needs to review

08:33.138 --> 08:34.514
so he can hang me higher,
probably.

08:34.598 --> 08:36.016
(SIGHS)

08:37.601 --> 08:40.938
Listen, um...
Stay away from this.

08:41.146 --> 08:42.773
If you're going
after another job,

08:42.898 --> 08:44.775
being seen with me is not
gonna help your chances.

08:46.193 --> 08:47.277
That's right.

08:47.402 --> 08:48.820
But it doesn't matter.

08:48.946 --> 08:50.948
I'm... I'm done
with law enforcement.

08:51.073 --> 08:53.283
Now, don't say that.
You're a good cop.

08:55.619 --> 08:57.120
Deena?

08:59.039 --> 09:00.374
What happened?

09:02.209 --> 09:04.544
Just had my eyes opened.

09:04.628 --> 09:06.922
Politics and lies,
that's all this job is,
right?

09:07.047 --> 09:08.799
You know that.
Pumpkin.

09:09.049 --> 09:11.677
Look, why don't we, uh,
have lunch?

09:12.427 --> 09:14.096
You can tell me
what's on your mind.

09:14.179 --> 09:15.430
(CELL PHONE RINGS)

09:17.307 --> 09:18.809
(SIGHS)
I got to take this.

09:18.892 --> 09:20.686
I... rain check.

09:21.061 --> 09:22.980
Yeah?
What... what now?

09:26.525 --> 09:28.777
Senator Bailey Brown,

09:28.986 --> 09:31.113
also known as
the Cobalt Knight,

09:31.196 --> 09:34.866
was found murdered
in his Los Angeles office
this morning,

09:35.409 --> 09:36.493
head crushed.

09:36.576 --> 09:39.329
The pathologist on scene
called TOD

09:39.413 --> 09:41.331
at roughly 24 hours ago.

09:41.415 --> 09:43.500
That puts him dead
early Thursday morning.

09:44.710 --> 09:47.087
He's a senator,
so where's the FBI?

09:47.587 --> 09:48.755
Gone.

09:49.047 --> 09:51.341
The FBI have
Retro Girl's killer.

09:51.425 --> 09:53.176
The accomplice
is already dead,

09:53.260 --> 09:55.470
and the drainer is back
in our possession.

09:56.304 --> 09:57.848
What about Conrad Moody?

09:57.931 --> 10:00.809
CROSS: That's being treated
as a suicide for now.

10:00.892 --> 10:02.936
As far as I'm concerned,
the little fuck...

10:03.020 --> 10:05.105
Strictly off record,

10:05.188 --> 10:06.440
got what he deserved.

10:07.357 --> 10:09.818
The senator was a Power.

10:09.901 --> 10:12.362
His anti-Powers legislation
made enemies.

10:12.654 --> 10:14.740
The murder happened
on our turf.

10:15.240 --> 10:18.160
We are expected
to do our job.

10:18.243 --> 10:20.203
So, Walker,
you and Pilgrim

10:20.287 --> 10:22.497
get over
to the federal building.

10:23.915 --> 10:25.042
It's ours?

10:25.208 --> 10:27.044
Sure, until you fuck it up.

10:28.253 --> 10:29.463
So don't fuck it up.

10:29.546 --> 10:30.589
Miss you.

10:30.881 --> 10:33.133
You okay?
Yeah, fine.

10:33.216 --> 10:34.926
Glad to be back.

10:37.929 --> 10:39.056
(BELL DINGS)

10:39.389 --> 10:41.391
(POP MUSIC PLAYING)

10:44.686 --> 10:45.896
Hi.

10:47.439 --> 10:48.899
You're that PTB lady.

10:49.191 --> 10:50.942
Nicole Glantz.
How are you?

10:51.068 --> 10:52.152
Nervous.

10:52.235 --> 10:53.820
When you're around,
shit happens.

10:53.904 --> 10:55.238
Comes with the job.

10:55.322 --> 10:56.907
What's your name?
Nope.

10:56.990 --> 10:58.116
That's cool.

10:58.241 --> 10:59.785
Don't blame you.

10:59.993 --> 11:03.080
I'm wondering if you could
identify someone for me.

11:03.789 --> 11:05.332
Do you know what this is from?

11:06.917 --> 11:08.502
Yeah, it's that
senator's sex tape.

11:08.585 --> 11:10.670
Do you know who that is?

11:12.589 --> 11:16.593
I'm told this place has
the best cosplay gear in town,

11:16.718 --> 11:19.179
and that Retro Girl outfit
is top of the line.

11:19.638 --> 11:20.806
Did you sell it?

11:21.098 --> 11:22.682
I'm not the only one
that works here.

11:22.766 --> 11:25.143
So give me their names.

11:25.268 --> 11:26.853
If they know
who this woman is,

11:26.937 --> 11:28.980
I'll give them the $500.

11:34.611 --> 11:35.946
Yeah, she shops here.

11:36.530 --> 11:39.407
Uh, name and address.

11:42.202 --> 11:43.620
I'll get it for you.
(DOOR BELL RINGS)

11:43.703 --> 11:45.288
We'll be waiting.

11:48.750 --> 11:49.793
It's Pelham.

11:49.876 --> 11:51.628
He's breaking a story
on Senator Brown.

11:51.878 --> 11:54.214
That fucking bastard.
What'd I miss?

11:55.090 --> 11:57.509
It's a stunning
and horrifically tragic end

11:57.634 --> 11:58.927
to a once-great Power

11:59.010 --> 12:00.345
who devoted his life

12:00.470 --> 12:02.639
to the preservation
of law and order.

12:02.764 --> 12:05.308
Senator Bailey Brown,
formerly the Cobalt Knight,

12:05.392 --> 12:07.352
was found murdered in his
Los Angeles office

12:07.477 --> 12:09.062
early this morning.

12:09.146 --> 12:10.647
PTB and I will continue
to follow this story

12:10.730 --> 12:12.149
wherever it leads,

12:12.274 --> 12:13.608
bringing you every
twist and turn,

12:13.692 --> 12:15.527
lifting any rock we find

12:15.652 --> 12:18.113
to expose those responsible.

12:18.196 --> 12:19.906
Some psycho with
an axe to grind

12:20.031 --> 12:22.284
had something to do
with this gruesome end

12:22.367 --> 12:23.535
to a tarnished hero,

12:24.035 --> 12:27.289
and no one will keep me
from bringing you the truth.

12:29.082 --> 12:31.376
(AIRPLANE ENGINES DRONING)

12:33.503 --> 12:35.839
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

12:42.345 --> 12:43.388
Patrick?

12:47.517 --> 12:48.768
How are you feeling?

12:50.562 --> 12:52.189
Is there anything you need?

12:53.773 --> 12:55.400
I don't know you.

12:55.817 --> 12:57.360
Yes, I'm new.

12:58.445 --> 12:59.821
I haven't been
at this very long,

12:59.905 --> 13:01.865
and I get the impression
that you're just starting.

13:02.490 --> 13:03.742
I know.

13:04.367 --> 13:05.869
Your head is buzzing.

13:06.578 --> 13:08.246
You're probably scared.

13:09.164 --> 13:10.749
My name is Janice.

13:11.875 --> 13:13.418
And I'm not really a nurse.

13:14.878 --> 13:16.671
You have the doctors
mystified.

13:16.755 --> 13:18.173
A lot of people
don't understand

13:18.256 --> 13:19.591
how you did what you did.

13:19.716 --> 13:21.134
It was wrong.

13:21.927 --> 13:23.220
It was necessary.

13:24.304 --> 13:26.139
You don't understand.

13:42.280 --> 13:43.615
Yes, I do.

13:45.283 --> 13:46.576
Who are you?

13:47.661 --> 13:48.954
May I sit down?

13:54.709 --> 13:56.419
Someone just like you.

14:01.174 --> 14:02.300
I'm a freak.

14:02.509 --> 14:04.094
You're a miracle...

14:04.636 --> 14:06.763
One of many...

14:06.846 --> 14:08.765
All of them capable
of changing the world.

14:09.099 --> 14:11.476
The world should end if all
we do is slaughter each other.

14:11.810 --> 14:14.312
We're here to make sure
that doesn't happen.

14:14.437 --> 14:17.399
People like you,
like us...

14:18.108 --> 14:19.484
People who can make
a difference,

14:19.609 --> 14:22.153
who can stop
this madness...

14:22.279 --> 14:24.114
We can change things.

14:24.906 --> 14:27.242
Nothing good
can come from this,

14:27.325 --> 14:29.286
not ever.

14:29.411 --> 14:31.162
You need to
get away from me.

14:31.288 --> 14:32.789
Patrick, I know what you're
going through right now--

14:32.872 --> 14:34.916
Not another word.
You go, or I will make you go.

14:35.000 --> 14:36.501
And you don't want that.

14:41.756 --> 14:43.133
Until next time.

14:43.216 --> 14:45.093
There won't be one.

14:45.969 --> 14:47.679
There will.

14:49.014 --> 14:50.473
I promise.

15:20.503 --> 15:22.213
(POLICE RADIO CHATTER)

15:25.842 --> 15:27.844
I don't think I can do this.

15:33.433 --> 15:34.809
Hello?

15:37.687 --> 15:39.064
You can.

15:39.189 --> 15:40.607
Being a cop comes
naturally to you.

15:42.317 --> 15:45.612
Then naturally, I should be
arresting your ass

15:45.695 --> 15:47.697
for murdering Conrad Moody.

15:47.947 --> 15:50.283
Well, there's the law,
and then there's...

15:50.367 --> 15:51.743
Uh-uh.
...what's right.

15:51.868 --> 15:54.371
There's just... the law.

15:54.913 --> 15:56.539
You believe in justice,
Deena.

15:56.915 --> 15:58.792
Sure, but not at
the cost of my soul!
Oh.

16:09.511 --> 16:11.513
Hey, you're in the car,

16:11.596 --> 16:13.640
on your way
to a crime scene

16:13.723 --> 16:15.392
with your partner.

16:18.478 --> 16:20.063
We're gonna be fine.

16:23.900 --> 16:25.276
Right?

16:26.069 --> 16:27.445
(SIGHS)

16:29.739 --> 16:31.074
Right.

16:31.950 --> 16:34.077
For a genius, you had
no sense of organization.

16:34.411 --> 16:37.622
You use the alphabet.
Use numbers,
for Christ's sake.

16:37.789 --> 16:39.624
Use something.

16:39.916 --> 16:41.960
Apparently,
he's using you.

16:42.085 --> 16:44.546
(SIGHS) Good morning.

16:44.629 --> 16:46.214
Good morning.
You made coffee.

16:46.381 --> 16:47.632
I did.

16:47.841 --> 16:49.759
And you brought sunshine.
(LAUGHING)

16:51.511 --> 16:52.679
Aren't you working it?

16:53.346 --> 16:55.014
How's our house guest?

16:55.390 --> 16:57.392
Calista is still sleeping,

16:57.475 --> 16:59.436
and she hasn't slept
in weeks.

16:59.769 --> 17:01.354
Yeah, she's been
through a lot.

17:01.688 --> 17:03.731
She's gonna flip
when she hears
about Senator Brown.

17:05.066 --> 17:07.694
Two-thirds of the original
Unity now dead.

17:07.986 --> 17:10.780
Well, I don't think SuperShock
has anything to worry about.

17:10.947 --> 17:12.365
And here I was
thinking "New Unity"

17:12.449 --> 17:13.491
might be a good name for us.

17:13.616 --> 17:14.784
(LAUGHING) What?

17:14.909 --> 17:17.620
Be like calling ourselves
"Tempting Fate."

17:18.121 --> 17:19.706
Well, there's
no rush, right?

17:19.789 --> 17:21.458
We still have a lot
to figure out here.

17:21.541 --> 17:24.043
No, no, no.
Not sure I agree with that.

17:24.544 --> 17:26.129
There's a Power
vacuum, Zora,

17:26.212 --> 17:28.381
and it's gonna be filled
by whatever gets there first,

17:28.465 --> 17:30.049
bad shit included.

17:30.467 --> 17:33.052
I think we need to let
the public know
that we're here

17:33.303 --> 17:35.472
and that we stand
between them and chaos.

17:36.431 --> 17:38.975
Wow, that's all great,

17:39.058 --> 17:41.144
but who's "we"?

17:41.478 --> 17:43.271
You, me, and Calista?

17:43.354 --> 17:45.523
Yeah, we're not ready
for anything like that.

17:45.648 --> 17:46.900
Triphammer thought we were.

17:46.983 --> 17:49.027
No, Triphammer thought
we had potential.

17:49.819 --> 17:51.488
There's a difference.

17:52.655 --> 17:54.616
So we need to maximize
our potential.

17:54.782 --> 17:56.034
Okay, now you're talking.

17:56.159 --> 17:57.410
How do we do that?

17:57.660 --> 17:59.496
Not alone.

17:59.579 --> 18:01.206
We need
a commanding officer.

18:01.623 --> 18:02.624
(LAUGHS) Okay.

18:02.707 --> 18:04.751
Let's dial the military
down a bit.

18:05.210 --> 18:07.545
Basically, a coach,
someone with experience.

18:07.879 --> 18:10.507
Experience at being
